<!DOCTYPE html><html âš¡><head> <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-head.ejs %><link rel="canonical" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Usermanual"></head><body class="home"> <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-header.ejs %><div class="wrap"><div class="container main"> <% include ../_partials/content/_bluenav-8015.ejs %><section class="blade get-started"><div class="container"><h1 class="post-title">IN-8015 HD User Manual</h1><div class="card-container"><div class="onecard"><div class="image"><p><amp-youtube data-videoid="Di5mbjn5rfU" layout="responsive" width="480" height="270"></amp-youtube></p><div class="action"><p class="justify">The IN-8015 HD is the first INSTAR HD 1080p pan &amp; tilt camera with an integrated infrared motion detector. The camera can easily be controlled through your smartphone from inside your network and also over the internet.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="card-container"><div class="onecard"><div class="image"><a href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Point2Point"><amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/P2P_Box.png" width="900" height="650" layout="responsive"></amp-img></a><div class="action"><p>Connect your camera to your local WiFi network by just pressing the <strong>WPS</strong> button (WiFi Protected Setup) and access your camera over the internet by scanning the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Network/Remote_Access/">P2P QR Code</a> with our <a href="/Software/iOS/InstarVision/iPhone/P2P">iPhone</a>, <a href="/Software/iOS/InstarVision/iPad/P2P">iPad</a>, <a href="/Software/Android/InstarVision/P2P">Android</a>, <a href="/Software/Windows/InstarVision/Windows_Phone/P2P">Windows Phone</a> and <a href="/Software/Windows/InstarVision/Metro/P2P">Windows (Metro)</a>.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="card-container"><div class="twocard"><div class="image"><a href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Lense_Adjustment"><amp-img noloading height=400 width=400 layout=responsive src="/images/QL-Box_Lense-Adjust_IN-8015HD.png"></amp-img></a></div><div class="action"><h4>Adjust your cameras focal point by simply turning the lense</h4><p class="justify">Your camera will be adjusted to perform straight out of the box in general surveillance settings. For indoor surveillance this means that the lense is set to give you a sharp image of distance up to 5m. For special needs just <a href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Lense_Adjustment">turn the lense</a> and keep an eye on your live video - the lense can be adjusted for a near-focus down to a few centimeters or for a near infinity focus for tele-observations.</p></div></div><div class="twocard"><div class="image"><a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/System/User/"><amp-img noloading height=400 width=400 layout=responsive src="/images/QL-Box_User_IN-6014HD.png"></amp-img></a></div><div class="action"><h4>Add a password to protect your privacy.</h4><p class="justify">Please make sure to change the default username and password before forwarding your camera to the internet. Change the password for <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/System/User/">ll 3 user classes</a> - administrator, user and visitor - to make sure nobody is able to connect to your camera without your permission. You can use the cameras <a href="/Products/1080p/Camera_Reset">hardware reset</a>, in case you forgot your password.<br><br><br></p></div></div></div><div class="card-container"><div class="onecard"><div class="image"><a href="/Internet_Access/Port_Forwarding"><amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/Portforwarding_Box.png" width="900" height="650" layout="responsive"></amp-img></a><div class="action"><p>In general we have to differentiate between two types of connections. One connection is the internal access which with we access the WebUI of the camera. This means that the computer as well as the camera are running in the same network and are most likely connected to the same router. You can then connect to the camera using the private IP address of the camera. The other connection is the external access to open the WebUI of the camera from outside your network. With this connection you can allow the access from anywhere in the world to your camera. No matter if you are sitting in the train using a smartphone or if you are on holidays using a laptop to access.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="card-container"><div class="twocard"><div class="image"><a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Alarm/Areas/"><amp-img noloading height=400 width=400 layout=responsive src="/images/QL-Box_MotionDetection_IN-6014HD.png"></amp-img></a></div><div class="action"><h4>Motion Detection and Video Recording</h4><p class="justify">Use your cameras internal image analysis in <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Alarm/Actions/">combination with the integrated heat detector (PIR)</a> to efficiently detect people, animals or cars - while moving trees, passign clouds or automatically switched light sources are ignored. Set your camera to start a video or snapshot recording on the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Features/SD_Card/">local SD card</a> and upload those files to an off-site <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Network/FTP/">FTP server</a>.<br></p></div></div><div class="twocard"><div class="image"><a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Alarm/Actions/"><amp-img noloading height=400 width=400 layout=responsive src="/images/QL-Box_Notification_IN-6014HD.png"></amp-img></a></div><div class="action"><h4>Email and Push Notification</h4><p class="justify">Set up your camera to detect motion to send you emails or push a notification to your smartphone. <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Alarm/Push_Service/">Push notifications</a> (<a href="/Software/iOS/InstarVision">iOS</a>, <a href="/Software/Android/InstarVision">Android</a> and <a href="/Software/Windows/InstarVision/Windows_Phone">Windows Phone</a>) will reach you in an instance. While the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Alarm/Actions/">email notification</a> might take a while, but added the bonus of attached snapshots. Activate both functions to be always informed about what is going on when you are on the road.<br><br></p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div><section class="blade blog mobile-down"><div class="container wider"><div class="row"><div class="twelve columns"><h1>Table of Topics</h1></div></div><div class="tab-container"><a class="tab" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Safety_Warnings"><h3>Safety Warnings</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Product_Features"><h3>Product Features</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Quick_Installation"><h3>Quick Installation</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series"><h3>Web User Interface</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Quick_Installation/WebUI_And_Firmware_Upgrade"><h3>Software Update</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Video_Streaming"><h3>Video Streaming</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Camera_Reset"><h3>Camera Reset</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Lense_Adjustment"><h3>Lense Adjustment</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Technical_Specifications"><h3>Technical Specifications</h3></a><a class="tab" href="/Indoor_Cameras/IN-8015_HD/Warranty"><h3>Warranty &amp; Disposal</h3></a></div> <a href="/Products/Usermanuals" target="_blank">VIEW MORE</a></div></section><footer> <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-footer.ejs %></footer></body></html>